Business Mogul, Mr. Gbenga Olawepo-Hashim has congratulated the newly appointed Chief of Staff (CoS) to the President, Professor Ibrahim Gambari, describing him as a globally acclaimed diplomat with  tremendous respect. Olawepo-Hashim who contested in last year’s presidential election commended President Muhammadu Buhari  for the appointment, adding that his wide range of experience would be brought to bear as a confidant. Meanwhile, the member representing Obokun/ Oriade Federal Constituency of Osun State Busayo Wole Oke, has described    Gambari’s appointment as the best decision President Buhari has made going by his global wealth of experience in administration spanning several years. Oke, in a statement yesterday in Abuja, said Nigerians would benefit immensely  from the appointment, adding that Nigerians should “not mind the negative opinions of some people against the new Chief of Staff for the nation to move forward.” Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here IPMAN lauds Buhari over Gambari's appointment Timi Frank, Prof. Sulaiman hail Gambari's appointment as COS Buhari’s Chief of Staff: Friends, colleagues  set agenda for Gambari